description: Almost 50 years since it was first broadcast on British television, Doctor Who is the longest running science-fiction television series of all time - and one of the most beloved. The secret to its longevity is its unique ability to recast the lead actor every few years. But who are the people behind 'The Doctor?' The Cast of Doctor Who takes you back in time to learn about the personal histories of William Hartnell, Tom Baker, Paul McGann, and the newest incarnation of The Doctor: Matt Smith. Plus, the Book Market edition features a bonus biography of Peter Cushing, the legendary actor who portrayed the Doctor in two theatrical films made in the 1960s!
name: The Cast of Dr. Who

volume.name: Fame: The Cast of Dr. Who

description:
What is SLEEPER? SLEEPER is the story of a man doing his job. A man who gets pushed in over his head. It's the story of deep-cover agent Holden Carver and the secret criminal organization he becomes enmeshed with, and of the deadly game of cat-and-mouse he plays with Tao, the amoral master of manipulation.Find out what elite readers already know: SLEEPER is the best book of its kind on the stands today. Don't be left out in the cold. What is SLEEPER?

"SLEEPER is a fantastic read, probably the best crime comic being published today" - ComicBookGalaxy.com "

SLEEPER could hold its own against any noir, from any medium...Brubaker is without a doubt the best crime fiction writer in comics today. " - Ain't It Cool News.com

"Quite possibly the most underrated title on the racks today...SLEEPER delivers non-stop entertainment from cover to cover!" - Wizard magazine
name: Book 1

description: Collecting the second half of SLEEPER Season One (issues #7-12), one of the most critically acclaimed comics of the year! Holden Carver is a man caught between two worlds; a former high-ranking agent for a covert government agency who was forced into a deadly undercover mission with no way back in from the cold. Now agent Carver lives one day at a time, trying to elude detection and not be found as...what? A good guy?
name: Book 2

description: A thrilling new collection featuring SLEEPER SEASON TWO #1-6! Lynch is back in Holden's life and trying to bring him back to the side of the angels. But is it too late for Holden's soul to be saved? And if it's not, can Lynch even be trusted, since Holden is little more than a pawn in the great game of super-powered espionage?
name: Book 3

description: Jack Kirby was the king of comics, and his impact on entertainment is still being felt today. Read the story of how he started in the slums of New York City, went on to be used by an industry he helped to create, and ended up in the hearts of people worldwide.
name: The Man Who Was the King

description: Collecting the final chapter of the SLEEPER saga, Vol. 2 #7-12! The endgame is in play and the fates of Carver, Lynch and the mysterious Tao are all up for grabs. It's winner take all…and the stakes are deadly!
name: Book 4

description:
In the year 2088 of the new datation system, the vigilace and security agencies defend the citizens from crime and the most important among them is the Alpha Agency, directed by Edward Reiser. Nathan Never and Legs Weaver are always first in line, helped by Sigmund Baginov and his amazing supercomputer. But what's his secret? What is hidden in the basement of Alfa Building?

Not a reboot, but a new starting point for the series, with an adventure set in the first days of the Alpha Agency...
name: Il segreto di Sigmund

description: In the Town Without Pity, good men are hard to find. Enter Wallace, a man of mystery. He's a nice guy who's very good at killing people. Out for an evening drive along the beach, he meets the woman of his dreams - and she's trying to kill herself. Why? And who are the shadowy cabal of power brokers who wrench her from his arms? When will all hell break loose?

In a quiet winter resort on Slovenian Alps, Harlan and his friends get to know the Twist Contest Organization... It’s not a dance competition, though: it’s a group of vigilantes. Our vampire hunters, sponsored by their friend Bobby Quintana, finds themselves enlisted to fight the undead who guard an opium plantation in Laos, owned by the “Triad of the Two Hundred Tigers”. But in the jungle there’s a surprise in wait for them: the arms washed in Dampyr’s blood are useless against their monster enemies, the Bayang, transformed in lethal weapons by the cruel Berbalang, Ladan Bat. Harlan Draka, too, will be tainted by the bite of a Bayang...
name: Soldati di ventura

description: On San Pietro Island, in Sardinia, Sophie Mutter found in a cave a graffito with the ancient symbol of the Tau. Apparently, it's proof that, as the tradition goes, the survivors of the legendary Children's Crusade took shelter in the Sardinian isle. Harlan recalls what Caleb once told him about the beginning of the harsh clash between himself and the Master of the Night, Nergal, that took place just in that occasion. Forced by Harlan, who accuses him to conceal too many crucial secrets, Caleb evokes an old episode of his long life on Earth– it happened during the XIII century, when he accompanied the crazed voyage of a children's army throughout Europe, between a myriad of adventures, battles, miracles and meetings with bandits, false beggars, pirates, Muslim warriors and, of course, Nergal himself with the terrifying demons of the infernal secret police...
name: Il viaggio dei folli

description: Kurjak’s father is dying. Before passing away, he wants to see again the old Mostar bridge, destroyed during the Yugoslavian Civil War and recently rebuilt. Miklos Kurjak is linked to that old bridge by a romantic and adventurous memory of his youth. Emil accepts to fulfill his dad’s desire, putting him in an ambulance with two of his cousins, a nurse and, obviously, Harlan and Tesla. In midwinter, they set out on the journey through the Bosnian mountain roads. It will be a journey in the past for all the passengers, where each one of them will find out a link with the magical bridge, created by a magnificent craftsman who worked for the Sultan. Tesla will see again Gorka and Shrek, the Masters of the Night that made her an undead. Kurjak will meet his dead comrades-in-arms, and his thoughts will go back to war’s hard choices. And Harlan, facing his past again – from his first encounter with Yuri to his experiences as a vagrant dampyr – will be able to shed a new light on his destiny and on the forces that had always been scheming behind his back, until the final clash against one of his worst enemies...
name: La leggenda del vecchio ponte

description: Often, a man’s most dangerous enemy is a rejected lover. The eccentric, well-read and mercurial Lady Lamb managed to conquer the attention of young poet George Byron, coveted by all the women of London’s high society. But their love will last for just one spring. Before Byron’s flight to Switzerland with the Shelleys and Dr. Polidori, the vindictive Lady Lamb steals from him a ring that he was presented with – during a trip to Middle East – by a strange former college mate of his in Cambridge, Augustus Darvell. The ring contains an organic parcel of the Master of the Night, Marsden, Lord of the Islands. The beautiful Caroline, after becoming the Master’s mistress, spies on Byron and his travel companions on behalf of her lover. The group is targeted by the ruthless vampire, eager to exact his revenge on the friends of his main enemy, Draka!
name: Il segreto di Lady Lamb

description: Comic artists are the creators of dreams. Advertising designer in a firm in Barcellona, Duarte spends the nights at his drawing table, dreaming of becoming an author of comic books. But the monsters and ghosts of his imagination begin to roam the city... An intervention by Harlan, Kurjak and Tesla could not be enough against the forces of Evil, especially if their leader is the gorgeous and treacherous Lady Nahema. Inside Duarte’s fantasy, though, there’s also an invincible superhero...
name: Shadowman

description: Due to the tangled strands of destiny, worthy of a story by Borges or Cortazar, old Uriarte Iberra discovers he has a “double” in the shape of young Antonio Peltzer, thirty years younger than himself. Up to now, Antonio’s life has been identical to his, from the astonishing physical resemblance to the mysterious murder of their fathers, when they were both kids. But, if Antonio’s life is destined to replicate Uriarte’s, them he will shortly have to accidentally kill his twin, Evaristo, who, in turn, is being hounded by a strange family of avengers. According to Argentinean folklore, the seventh child of a family will turn into a werewolf. Evaristo is a seventh child. And, along the roads of Bueons Aires, Harklan Draka is trying to put spokes in the wheels of the “lycanthrope hunters”…
name: I cacciatori di licantropi

description: Chile, from Santiago’s back alleys to the beaches of Viña del Mar, from the Atacama desert to the Andes peaks, is the scenery for the hunt to the Condor, a Master of the Night who was an ally of the Argentinean dictatorship and of the Chilean “golpistas”. This powerful vampire is now getting rid of his former accomplices and other dangerous witnesses, with the help of the young killer, Erwin Rogers. Arriving just in time to prevent the execution of a journalist, Guerrero, Harlan, Kurjak & Tesla join a squad of brave policemen and escape on a northbound route
name: I giorni del Condor

description: Hounded by Condor’s un-dead and by the corrupt carabineros in Condor’s pay, Harlan and his buddies have two priorities. First: staying alive. Second: get Harlan to within a close distance of the elusive Master of the Night, so that he can kill the fiend with his Dampyr powers. But where is Condor hiding? The match is almost hopeless… Unless, that is, Guerrero the journalist and Rogers the killer are unconsciously in possession of some forgotten secret capable of turning the tables and taking our heroes to the final showdown, where there are no holds barred and every last drop of blood must be shed…
name: Nel deserto di Atacama

description:
From acclaimed 'Hulk' writer Greg Pak, legendary 'Walking Dead' producer Gale Ann Hurd, and Tony Parker, penciller of the Eisner-nominated 'Do Androids Dream of Electric Sheep', comes this winter's biggest blockbuster new series - DEAD MAN'S RUN! They call the prison 'Hell.' And they just might be right. The nation's toughest soldier heads into the world's most deadly maximum security lock-up and uncovers a world of terror and temptation beyond his darkest dreams. Featuring a brand-new 12-page story that sets the stage for next month's upcoming premiere of DEAD MAN'S RUN #1, make sure to get in on the ground floor of this newest exciting Aspen hit series! Complete with an additional sketchbook section showcasing the astounding artwork of series artist Tony Parker, never before seen character designs and sketches, and surrounded by a stunning new cover, this special zero issue is definitely not to be missed!

They call the prison "Hell." And they just might be right. The nation's toughest soldier heads into the world's most deadly maximum security lock-up and uncovers a world of terror and temptation beyond his darkest dreams.
name: Full Circle

description: The sixth issue of Cooper's brilliant series marks an adventurous departure from a successful formula. Subtitled Overbite: Paintings and Drawings of Mostly Pillowy Girls, this luxurious, full-color coffee table artbook doubles as the catalogue for a series of high-profile shows Cooper has been hosting in art galleries across North America, reprinting page after page of Cooper's disturbingly cute canvases of young women. Also featured is a hilariously insightful introduction by comedian David Cross (Mr. Show).
name: Overbite
